ased nutrient cycling can compensate for longitudinal declines in nutrient concentrations in stream water, preventing large longitudinal changes in periphyton biomass and productivity. Nutrient cycling and algal species composition were the characteristics showing strongest longitudinal linkage in these periphyton-dominated streams, whereas total biomass and productivity patterns were poorly related to longitudinal position.},
